# Component inventory — reuse before creating

If you reach for one of these capabilities, use the existing component.

| Capability | Component |
|---|---|
| Multi-value text/email input with chips | [src/lib/components/email-chips-editor.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/email-chips-editor.svelte) |
| Destructive confirm with typed message | [src/lib/components/confirm-dialog.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/confirm-dialog.svelte) |
| Entity create/edit form in a sheet | [src/lib/components/client-form-sheet.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/client-form-sheet.svelte) |
| Child-record (effective-dated) form sheet | [src/lib/components/rate-form-sheet.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/rate-form-sheet.svelte) |
| Global setting modal | [src/lib/components/default-cc-dialog.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/default-cc-dialog.svelte) |
| Single sheet shared by create + edit | [src/lib/components/time-entry-sheet.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/time-entry-sheet.svelte) |
| "Generate derived record" wizard | [src/lib/components/generate-invoice-sheet.svelte](mdc:src/lib/components/generate-invoice-sheet.svelte) |

shadcn primitives (Button, Input, Label, Select, Sheet, Dialog, Badge, Separator) live under `src/lib/components/ui/`.

## Patterns

- **Sheet vs Dialog**: forms → `Sheet` (full-screen on mobile, drawer on desktop). Confirmations and small pickers → `Dialog`. Default to `Sheet`.
- **Create + edit share one sheet**: take an optional `entity` prop; "create" mode = `entity == null`. See `time-entry-sheet.svelte`.
- **Bindable props for v-model-style state**: `let { open = $bindable(false), value = $bindable<T[]>([]) } = $props();`
- **Form actions inside components**: use `use:enhance` and call back to the page via `onSuccess` / `onError` callback props.
- **Svelte 5 runes**: `$state`, `$props`, `$bindable`, `$derived`, `$effect`. Do not use Svelte 4 reactive `$:` syntax.

## When to add a new component

- The pattern doesn't match any row in the inventory above
- A `.svelte` file exceeds ~150 lines
- The same JSX appears in 2+ pages

When you add one, update this rule.
